gomodel:SYNGO_1947  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 21/11/2017 Pim\nIn Fig.4+6+8+9 the authors show that:\n1. Fig.4: TFMPP (5-HT1B receptor agonist), reduced in a dose-related manner the amplitude of glutamatergic EPSCs evoked by stimulating selectively the optic nerve (hamster SCN)\n2. Fig.6: TFMPP had no effect on the amplitude of inward currents generated by local application of glutamate (hamster SCN)\n3. Fig.8+9: Effect of TFMPP on circadian rhythm (mediated by SCN) is not observed in 5-HT1B receptor knock-out mice (mouse brain). Experimental description: Fig.4+6: hamster SCN preparation\nFig.8+9: live mice\n- Human can also be made if needed." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1947" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10029" .

